## ðŸ”¹ Topic 1: Linear Search (Easy)
### Problem Statement
Given an integer array `nums` and an integer `target`, return the index of `target`.  
If the target does not exist, return `-1`.

### Constraints
- `1 â‰¤ nums.length â‰¤ 10^5`
- `-10^9 â‰¤ nums[i], target â‰¤ 10^9`

### Approach
Traverse the array sequentially and compare each element with the target.

### Time & Space Complexity
- **Time:** `O(n)`
- **Space:** `O(1)`

```java
class LinearSearch {
    static int search(int[] arr, int target) {
        if (arr == null || arr.length == 0) return -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] == target) return i;
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```

## ðŸ”¹ Topic 2: Search in Range (Easy)
### Problem Statement
Given an integer array nums, search for a target element only within a given index range [lower, upper].  
Return the index if found, otherwise return -1.

### Constraints
- `0 â‰¤ lower â‰¤ upper < nums.length`

### Approach
Apply linear search but restrict traversal to the given range.

### Time & Space Complexity
- **Time:** `O(n)`
- **Space:** `O(1)`

```java
class SearchInRange {
    static int search(int[] arr, int lower, int upper, int target) {
        if (arr == null || lower < 0 || upper >= arr.length || lower > upper)
            return -1;

        for (int i = lower; i <= upper; i++) {
            if (arr[i] == target) return i;
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```

## ðŸ”¹ Topic 3: Search in String (Easy)
### Problem Statement
Given a string s and a character target, determine whether the character exists in the string.

### Constraints
- `1 â‰¤ s.length â‰¤ 10^5`

### Approach
Iterate through each character and compare it with the target.

### Time & Space Complexity
- **Time:** `O(n)`
- **Space:** `O(1)`

```java
class SearchInString {
    static boolean search(String str, char target) {
        if (str == null) return false;

        for (char ch : str.toCharArray()) {
            if (ch == target) return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

## ðŸ”¹ Topic 4: Min & Max in Array (Easy)
### Minimum Element in Array
#### Problem Statement
Given an integer array, return the minimum element.

#### Approach
Track the smallest value while traversing the array.

#### Time & Space Complexity
- **Time:** `O(n)`
- **Space:** `O(1)`

```java
class MinInArray {
    static int min(int[] arr) {
        if (arr == null || arr.length == 0) return -1;

        int min = arr[0];
        for (int num : arr) {
            if (num < min) min = num;
        }
        return min;
    }
}
```

### Index of Maximum Element
#### Problem Statement
Given an integer array, return the index of the maximum element.

#### Approach
Track the index of the largest value while iterating.

#### Time & Space Complexity
- **Time:** `O(n)`
- **Space:** `O(1)`

```java
class MaxInArray {
    static int maxIndex(int[] arr) {
        if (arr == null || arr.length == 0) return -1;

        int maxIndex = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] > arr[maxIndex]) maxIndex = i;
        }
        return maxIndex;
    }
}
```

## ðŸ”¹ Topic 5: Array Manipulation (Easy)
### Reverse an Array
#### Problem Statement
Reverse the given array in-place without using extra space.

#### Approach
Use two pointers from start and end, swapping elements.

#### Time & Space Complexity
- **Time:** `O(n)`
- **Space:** `O(1)`

```java
class ReverseArray {
    static void reverse(int[] arr) {
        int start = 0, end = arr.length - 1;
        while (start < end) {
            int temp = arr[start];
            arr[start++] = arr[end];
            arr[end--] = temp;
        }
    }
}
```

### Swap Two Elements
#### Problem Statement
Swap two elements at given indices in an array.

```java
class SwapElements {
    static void swap(int[] arr, int i, int j) {
        int temp = arr[i];
        arr[i] = arr[j];
        arr[j] = temp;
    }
}
```

## ðŸ”¹ Topic 6: Binary Search (Easy â†’ Medium)
### Problem Statement
Given a sorted array (ascending or descending), find the index of a target element using binary search.

### Approach
Detect sorting order, then apply binary search accordingly.

### Time & Space Complexity
- **Time:** `O(log n)`
- **Space:** `O(1)`

```java
class BinarySearchCustom {
    static int binarySearch(int[] arr, int target) {
        int low = 0, high = arr.length - 1;
        boolean isAsc = arr[low] < arr[high];

        while (low <= high) {
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

            if (arr[mid] == target) return mid;

            if (isAsc) {
                if (target < arr[mid]) high = mid - 1;
                else low = mid + 1;
            } else {
                if (target > arr[mid]) high = mid - 1;
                else low = mid + 1;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```

## ðŸ”¹ Topic 7: 2D Arrays (Medium)
### Search in 2D Array
#### Problem Statement
Search for a target element in a jagged 2D array and return its position.

```java
class Search2DArray {
    static int[] search(int[][] arr, int target) {
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < arr[i].length; j++) {
                if (arr[i][j] == target)
                    return new int[]{i, j};
            }
        }
        return null;
    }
}
```

### Minimum Element Position in 2D Array

```java
class MinIn2DArray {
    static int[] minPosition(int[][] arr) {
        int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int[] pos = new int[2];

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < arr[i].length; j++) {
                if (arr[i][j] < min) {
                    min = arr[i][j];
                    pos[0] = i;
                    pos[1] = j;
                }
            }
        }
        return pos;
    }
}
```

## ðŸ”¹ Topic 8: LeetCode Problems (Medium)
### LeetCode 1295 â€“ Find Numbers with Even Number of Digits

```java
class EvenDigitNumbers {
    static int findNumbers(int[] nums) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            if (digits(num) % 2 == 0) count++;
        }
        return count;
    }

    static int digits(int num) {
        if (num == 0) return 1;
        num = Math.abs(num);

        int count = 0;
        while (num > 0) {
            num /= 10;
            count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

### LeetCode 1672 â€“ Richest Customer Wealth

```java
class RichestCustomerWealth {
    static int maximumWealth(int[][] accounts) {
        int max = 0;
        for (int[] customer : accounts) {
            int sum = 0;
            for (int money : customer) sum += money;
            max = Math.max(max, sum);
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```

## ðŸ”¹ Topic 9: ArrayList Basics (Easy)
### Problem Statement
Demonstrate basic operations on an ArrayList.

```java
class ArrayListExample {
    static void demo() {
        ArrayList<Long> list = new ArrayList<>();

        list.add(12L);
        list.add(12123456L);
        list.add(121234567L);

        list.remove(Long.valueOf(12123456L));

        System.out.println(list);
        System.out.println("Size: " + list.size());
        System.out.println("Index: " + list.indexOf(121234567L));
    }
}
```

